name: NataLee (JG)
description:
Natalie Lee, better known as NataLee, Instagram model and influencer.

I thought it was about time I gave my very first embedding a paint-job. When I created it, I thought it was a poor attempt because I didn't really know how TIs worked and I was building pretty poor prompts. In retrospect, I now think it was at least a very decent TI, and I'm not really sure this new version improves upon it. I'll let you judge.

The new version is an 1800-step TI. I removed 5 pics from the original dataset of 23 to leave it at 18, and applied my usual settings.

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

modelVersions.description:
My very first embedding. It had a tendency to depict NataLee as a brunette, but other than that I think it was a pretty good TI. I probably got kind of lucky, as I didn't really know most of what I was doing at the time. xD

According to the automatically generated log, these were the settings I used:

"num_of_dataset_images": 23,

"num_vectors_per_token": 5,

"embedding_name": "n4t4lee",

"learn_rate": "0.004",

"batch_size": 3,

"training_width": 512,

"training_height": 512,

"steps": 1500,

Unfortunately I don't know what gradient I used. I suspect it was gradient 1, but I'm not 100% sure about it.
